I love this pasta dish! I have made it over and over again and it always wins raves from friends. I change it slightly by adding a pre-cooked roux to the sauce to thicken it a little. I just cook a little flour and butter prior to starting the recipe, and put it in the refrigerator or freezer and add it later to the hot sauce. I also like to make the sauce and pasta ahead of time and combine them, and pop them in the oven just prior to guests arriving. Just cook the pasta, and toss with olive oil. Cool, and place in a zip lock bag in the refrigerator. An hour or two before guests arrive combine the sauce with the pasta and let come to room temperature. Bake in a 350 degree oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

