This is our favorite pasta dish, and I make it often. There are easy ways to lower the fat content. I substitute olive oil for the butter and instead of Italian sausage use the lower fat turkey sausage. To give the sauce some real substance, I don't use diced tomatoes but put in a 28 oz. can of whole tomatoes, which I quarter. I use about half the amount of cream called for and don't add the grated parmesan (instead, put the parmesan out on the table for people to add themselves). To boost the nutritional value and provide more color, I also add a bunch of broccoli rabe at the end (stems and all, chopped in 1 1/2 inch lengths and parboiled ahead of time). I'm not a broccoli rabe fan, but in this sauce it's great and so good for you!

