To the previous reviewers comment, thank you so much for the correction! I did in in fact mean evaporated milk. I hope I didn't turn too many recipes into a disaster with my mistake!

Rating: 4
RE: the dieticians recommendation for 'condensed milk'.... I'm pretty sure she meant Evaporated Skim Milk, which is quite a different thing from the very sweet stuff used for baking/candy making. Condensed milk is sugar/milk which is cooked together and makes a thick, sweet caramel-tasting 'milk'. Evaporated Skim/Nonfat Milk is just that... milk with some of the water added. I have used it successfully in many recipes calling for cream, but it does reduce the lovely round 'mouthfeel' that cream adds. What it does do is mimic the consistency and the appearance really well, and if fat is that much of an issue...try it again :) You might like it if you eat lowfat all the time, as 'cream' often tastes greasy to those on a lowfat regime. Good luck!

