I made this last night for dinner and my fianc and I LOVED it there was not a scrap left over! I did however make a few changes which I would suggest you Please follow. First don't cook the sausage with the onions and garlic. I cooked the sweet turkey sausage separately to avoid all the added grease. I sauted the onions and garlic with some red pepper flakes then added the white wine and then added the cooked sausage. Also you definitely need more tomatoes to form a sauce. I used the one can of diced tomatoes and then added half of a can of whole tomatoes which I broke up with a spoon.....cook for about 10 minutes then I added only half a cup of cream this is really all you need. Cook a little while longer and then added a few pinches of flour to make it a little thicker. It was simply delicious. A rich creamy tomato sauce with a kick was the result and also there was not too much fat what more could you ask for!

