I couldn't find italian sausage anywhere and so replaced it with polish sausage - and it was delicious. We eat a lot of pasta and usually use store-bought sauces. This recipe was so easy to follow, it turned out beautifully. When I was halfway through making it, I thought "Boy, there's a lot here" (I was only cooking for two) and when I finished cooking it, I turned the page and it said 'Serves 6' - still, my husband was more than happy to eat it heated up for two more days!

Rating: 4
This is a simple, yummy and satisfying dish. As a twist, I use half hot/half sweet sausage in the sauce. Also, I cook the pasta, place in a large casserole, cover with the sauce, then sprinkle the cheese on top and bake at 325 for about 20-25 minutes. Makes a hearty casserole that lasts for several meals (for 2)

Rating: 3
My husband loved it and the kids ate it too!! I recommend that you saute the onions and garlic at a lower temperature and then up the temperature when you add the sausage. At medium high the onions and garlic cook too fast and they are hard to manage with that little amount of oil and butter. I agree that increasing the amount of onions would be beneficial, but unless you really like garlic I would leave that at 3 cloves. This dish is delicious, very filling and "something different"!!

